message.content: cs.IT, cs.IT is the most likely category as the paper deals with information theory and specifically the R\'enyi entropy. Other likely categories could be cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) as the entropy power inequality has applications in data compression and coding theory, cs.SI (social and information networks) as entropy measures are used in network analysis, cs.LG (machine learning) as entropy measures are used in information theory and statistical learning, and cs.NA (numerical analysis) as the paper involves mathematical analysis and inequalities.
